 Former Super Eagles forward, Odion Ighalo has left Manchester United following the expiration of his contract with the Premier League side. The Nigerian extended his loan from Shanghai Greenland Shenhua which was initially due to end on 31 May to 30 January 2021. Ighalo took to his social media handle to pen a goodbye letter to the Red Devils, fans and everyone that supported him through his journey at Old Trafford. Ighalo is a boyhood fan of Manchester United and scored five goals in his time at the club. Post Views: 
				61